{"key":"processedPost-13168486","value":{"id":13168486,"first":13164484,"last":13169066,"when":1284011533,"utime":"09/09/10 08:52 AM","content":"Yes, but get a small screwdriver.&nbsp; One intended for eyeglasses works well.&nbsp; I usually use warm water on the towel because it works faster.&nbsp; You'll also need to re-calibrate weekly, because the cheap bastards they pawn on us these days won't stay calibrated.<br /><br /><blockquote>Quote:<br />In the PF Tek video after the cakes are first initially put into the SG terrarium, RR waits 30 mins and then sprays the hell out of the cakes (like 30+ sprays). My question is this: does he spray that much <br /></blockquote><br /><br />To hydrate the dry verm and get it nice and moist.&nbsp; You wait the 30 minutes because if you spray hard right after you roll in dry verm, the verm will fall off.&nbsp; By waiting, the verm stays attached to the cake when you spray.<br /><br />Once you've hydrated the verm, you mist lightly a few times per day as necessary to keep it moist, but you won't have to spray as much as the first time.<br />RR","title":"Re: Calibrating Hygrometer","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}